## 🛡️ Security

### What Was Done

#### 1. [.env](file:///Users/huzaifa/DevZoro/seatech/.env) in [.gitignore](file:///Users/huzaifa/DevZoro/seatech/.gitignore)
The [.env](file:///Users/huzaifa/DevZoro/seatech/.env) file is listed in [.gitignore](file:///Users/huzaifa/DevZoro/seatech/.gitignore) — secrets are never auto-committed.

#### 2. Git History Purge (March 2026)
A **service role JWT** was found hardcoded in [check-db.mjs](file:///Users/huzaifa/DevZoro/seatech/check-db.mjs) and [check-rls.mjs](file:///Users/huzaifa/DevZoro/seatech/check-rls.mjs) (debug scripts committed to GitHub).

**Remediation:**
- Used `git filter-repo` to rewrite all 13 commits in history
- Replaced the leaked JWT with `***REDACTED***` across entire history
- Force-pushed the purged history to GitHub (`git push --force`)
- Removed hardcoded keys from both files; replaced with `process.env` reads
- Verified: `0 occurrences` of the leaked key remain

#### 3. RLS on `dealer_applications` (March 2026)
The table had no RLS enabled despite having policies defined in the migration.
- Ran `ALTER TABLE public.dealer_applications ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;` directly in Supabase SQL Editor
- Cleaned up duplicate policies left from multiple runs
- Final state: exactly 3 clean policies in place

#### 4. Robots.txt — Blocks Admin Routes
`/admin`, `/dashboard`, `/auth`, `/cart` are blocked from search engine indexing.

#### 5. Role-Based Access Control
- Admin panel is double-protected: [ProtectedRoute](file:///Users/huzaifa/DevZoro/seatech/src/components/ProtectedRoute.tsx#13-125) (client-side) + Supabase RLS + service role client (server-side)
- Normal users hitting `/admin` get a toast error and redirect — they never see admin data

